
[1]employment

   EMPLOY'MENT, n. The act of employing or using.

   1. Occupation; business; that which engages the head or hands; as
   agricultural employments; mechanical employments. Men, whose employment
   is to make sport and amusement for others, are always despised.

   2. Office; public business or trust; agency or service for another or
   for the public. The secretary of the treasury has a laborious and
   responsible employment. He is in the employment of government.
